{"title":"Brompton P Line takes classic “Superlight” folding bicycle to the next level","link":"https://bikerumor.com/brompton-p-line-takes-classic-superlight-folding-bicycle-to-the-next-level/","date":1639064772000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03184223/Brompton_P-Line_2021_7.jpg\" data-fancybox=\"\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03184223/Brompton_P-Line_2021_7-800x534.jpg\" alt=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03184223/Brompton_P-Line_2021_7-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03184223/Brompton_P-Line_2021_7-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03184223/Brompton_P-Line_2021_7-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03184223/Brompton_P-Line_2021_7-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03184223/Brompton_P-Line_2021_7-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03184223/Brompton_P-Line_2021_7.jpg 1600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"></a><header></header><p>Support us! BikeRumor may earn a small commission from affiliate links in this article. <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/privacy\" target=\"_blank\">Learn more</a>.</p></div><div role=\"main\"><article id=\"post-280030\" role=\"article\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/BlogPosting\"><section itemprop=\"text\"><p>For the past 16 years, Brompton’s Superlight folding commuter bike has been a mainstay in lightweight, portable urban bikes.</p><p>These bikes break down quickly into compact little packages that are a breeze to stow under a desk, carry into crowded buildings or tuck into the truck or back seat of a rideshare when your destination is a little too far to leg it out.</p><div id=\"attachment_280036\"><p><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-280036\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03184147/Brompton_P-line_2021_2.jpg\" alt=\"Woman carrying fully folded Brompton P Line bike.\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03184147/Brompton_P-line_2021_2.jpg 2000w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03184147/Brompton_P-line_2021_2-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03184147/Brompton_P-line_2021_2-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03184147/Brompton_P-line_2021_2-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03184147/Brompton_P-line_2021_2-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03184147/Brompton_P-line_2021_2-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px\"></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-280036\">The Brompton P Line weighs just over 21 pounds. Photo courtesy of Brompton.</p></div><p>In October, <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/brompton-re-launches-classic-folding-bike-range-in-simplified-a-c-electric-c-line-groups/\">Brompton relaunched its classic folding bike range</a> with new build options and simplified A, C and Electric C groups.</p><div id=\"attachment_280038\"><p><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-280038\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03184211/Brompton_P-line_2021_6.jpg\" alt=\"A man sitting on top of a Brompton P Line bike. Rear view.\" width=\"1333\" height=\"2000\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03184211/Brompton_P-line_2021_6.jpg 1333w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03184211/Brompton_P-line_2021_6-200x300.jpg 200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03184211/Brompton_P-line_2021_6-800x1200.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03184211/Brompton_P-line_2021_6-80x120.jpg 80w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03184211/Brompton_P-line_2021_6-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03184211/Brompton_P-line_2021_6-1024x1536.jpg 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1333px) 100vw, 1333px\"></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-280038\">Brompton’s P Line is latest Brompton model to get an overhaul. Photo courtesy of Brompton.</p></div><p>Brompton is chugging along in that drive for simplification by relaunching the Superlight as the P Line. But it’s far from the same bike.</p><p>The new P Line sticks with the lightweight focus of the previous Superlight, but this time with a redesigned titanium rear frame and a fork that shaves off 700 grams from its steel counterpart, making for easier riding or carrying.</p><div id=\"attachment_280032\"><p><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-280032\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03180736/Brompton_P-line_2021_4.jpg\" alt=\"Detail shot of the front of the Brompton P Line folding bike.\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03180736/Brompton_P-line_2021_4.jpg 2000w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03180736/Brompton_P-line_2021_4-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03180736/Brompton_P-line_2021_4-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03180736/Brompton_P-line_2021_4-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03180736/Brompton_P-line_2021_4-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03180736/Brompton_P-line_2021_4-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px\"></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-280032\">Brompton new P Line Bike aims to be a nimble, quick urban companion that goes anywhere you do. Photo courtesy of Brompton.</p></div><p>The P Line’s folded footprint is 25.3 x 23 x 10.6 inches. It weighs in at 21.27 pounds and comes in two colors: Storm Grey or Midnight Black.</p><p>Other features in the new P line include a redesigned suspension setup, a new wheelset, and a dual-locking seat post that can fully collapse for storage or extended so riders can use the seat as a handle and roll the bike along beside them in its folded position.</p><div id=\"attachment_280035\"><p><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-280035\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03184138/Brompton_P-line_2021_1.jpg\" alt=\"Man rolling Brompton P Line bike in folded position.\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03184138/Brompton_P-line_2021_1.jpg 2000w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03184138/Brompton_P-line_2021_1-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03184138/Brompton_P-line_2021_1-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03184138/Brompton_P-line_2021_1-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03184138/Brompton_P-line_2021_1-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03184138/Brompton_P-line_2021_1-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px\"></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-280035\">The Brompton P Line offers multiple seat post positions to assist with storage or rolling in urban environments. Photo courtesy of Brompton.</p></div><p>The bike comes with gearing focused on city riding, with a four-speed gear set that includes a 60-gram derailleur.</p><p>Brompton’s Chief Design and Engineering Officer Will Carleysmith said the improvements amount to a super lightweight bike that is both faster and easier to haul around the city than its predecessor.</p><p>“The new Brompton P Line is a leap forward from the Superlight, it is faster to ride, lighter to carry, and easier to move around the city in every way,” he said.</p><div id=\"attachment_280037\"><p><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-280037\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03184200/Brompton_P-line_2021_5.jpg\" alt=\"Photo of rear wheel and groupset of the Brompton P line bike while being ridden. Side view.\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03184200/Brompton_P-line_2021_5.jpg 2000w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03184200/Brompton_P-line_2021_5-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03184200/Brompton_P-line_2021_5-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03184200/Brompton_P-line_2021_5-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03184200/Brompton_P-line_2021_5-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03184200/Brompton_P-line_2021_5-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px\"></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-280037\">The Brompton P Line is faster than its “Superlight” predecessor, with a four-speed gear set. Photo courtesy of Brompton.</p></div><p><a href=\"https://us.brompton.com/\"><em>brompton.com</em></a></p></section></article></div></div>","author":"Mark Wilson","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"d2f85e024baac73c4ed29765fec972a61aa9ec4bab6ce5659bc68b9749ee1c5d","category":"Cycling"}